{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Qbc9fitbJgyZZK5SNgz2Nr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the source file and convert it to a knowledge file JSON.\n\n**Work Step 1: Identify the title**\nThe first heading underlined with `=====` is: \"変数に値を設定するsetタグ\"\n\n**Work Step 1.5: Check for no-knowledge-content**\nThe source has explanatory text about the set tag functionality - this is Layer A/B content. So `no_knowledge_content: false`.\n\n**Work Step 2: Build the section list**\nLooking at the source - there are no h2 headings (underlined with `-----`). The entire document is under one h1 heading. So this is a single section: s1.\n \n**Work Step 3: Extract section content**\n\nNow I'm going through each paragraph to classify its layer. The opening paragraph explains the purpose of storing values in variables for maintainability and introduces the set tag feature - that's foundational Layer C content. The reference to the tag itself is part of that same introductory explanation.\n\nThe second paragraph describes the attributes used in the set tag (var, value, name) - that's Layer B covering the component's specifications.\n\nThe third paragraph details the scope attribute and its options (request or page scope), with request being the default, and mentions when page scope is useful for shared UI components across the application.\n\nThe fourth paragraph explains how the set tag retrieves values when the name attribute is specified - it defaults to returning a single value, taking the first element if the value is an array or collection, though there are cases where you'd want to retrieve the entire array or collection as-is for shared UI components.\n\nFor those situations, I can set the bySingleValue attribute to false on the set tag to get the full collection. There's also an important warning that the set tag doesn't perform HTML escaping, so I need to use the write tag when outputting variables set this way. 名前衝突を避けるにはスコープを使い分けることが重要で、`bySingleValue`属性を`false`に設定すれば配列やコレクションをそのまま取得できる。JSPの例として、`setタグ`で変数を定義してから複数の場所で参照する使い方を示している。\n\n重要な注意点として、`setタグ`はHTMLエスケープ処理を行わないため、出力時には必ず`writeタグ`を使用する必要がある。\n\n次に、`n:set`タグの属性を整理している。`var`属性で変数名を指定し、`value`属性で直接値を設定するか、`name`属性でスコープ上のオブジェクトを参照する。`scope`属性ではリクエストスコープまたはページスコープを指定でき、未指定時はリクエストスコープが使用される。`bySingleValue`属性は`name`属性使用時に単一値として取得するかどうかを制御する。","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20880,"cache_read_input_tokens":29955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20880,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0ab210be-6f4c-4b81-8e2b-5760e776b7d2","uuid":"478b2068-adef-4761-9acb-f98412659363"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Qbc9fitbJgyZZK5SNgz2Nr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01QxUf4eyuYpk1yduWf4Z7TY","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"id":"libraries-07_OtherTag","title":"変数に値を設定するsetタグ","no_knowledge_content":false,"official_doc_urls":[],"index":[{"id":"s1","title":"変数に値を設定するsetタグ","hints":["n:set","n:write","WebView_SetTag","var属性","value属性","name属性","scope属性","bySingleValue属性","JSP変数設定","スコープ指定","ページスコープ","リクエストスコープ","HTMLエスケープ","配列・コレクション取得"]}],"sections":{"s1":"`n:set`タグ（:ref:`WebView_SetTag`）で変数に値を設定する。\n\n**属性**:\n- `var`: 変数名を指定\n- `value`: 直接値を指定する場合\n- `name`: リクエストスコープなどスコープ上のオブジェクトを参照する場合\n- `scope`: 変数を格納するスコープ（`request` または `page`）。未指定時はリクエストスコープに設定される\n- `bySingleValue`: `name`属性指定時にデフォルト（`true`）で単一値として取得。配列・コレクションをそのまま取得したい場合は`false`を指定\n\n**scope属性の使い分け**:\n- `request`（デフォルト）: 通常のケース\n- `page`: 共通利用UIパーツで他JSPの変数との名前衝突を防ぎたい場合\n\n```jsp\n<n:set var=\"title\" value=\"ユーザ情報登録\" />\n<head>\n    <title><n:write name=\"title\" /></title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1><n:write name=\"title\" /></h1>\n</body>\n```\n\n> **警告**: setタグはHTMLエスケープ処理を実施しない。setタグで設定した変数を出力する場合はwriteタグを使用すること。"}}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20880,"cache_read_input_tokens":29955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20880,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0ab210be-6f4c-4b81-8e2b-5760e776b7d2","uuid":"f5cb98a6-ac4f-4e04-a77a-9d284e4f79c6"}
